      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PATIENT VICKY (2) is progressing well with another good run, placing by 2.75 lengths (17.73) in a Grade 5 at this track. Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. Expected to feature in the finish again. DIVE RIGHT IN (1) scored two back then was always well back and could manage only a 13 length 7th at this track (18.54). Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. Cannot be underestimated. VERGLAS (4) scored off the inside draw two back then finished sixth last start off a wider box (18.29) at this track over 300m. Returns to the scene of her maiden win. Well placed here and should do much better. DOLLAR ROLEX (7) can improve on an unplaced run here last time out. Something for the Multiples: RACCOON RHIA (9)",
